Data Masking

What if we try to make a function that takes a data frame?


grouped_mean &lt;- function(df, group_var, mean_var) {
  df |&gt; 
    group_by(group_var) |&gt; 
    summarize(mean(mean_var))
}


diamonds |&gt; grouped_mean(cut, carat)

Error in `group_by()`:
! Must group by variables found in `.data`.
✖ Column `group_var` is not found.



When group_by and summarize are called, they treat group_var and mean_var literally as names of of variables to search for in data
Called data masking because real values of group_var and mean_var ignored

Embracing in Action

grouped_mean &lt;- function(df, group_var, mean_var) {
  df |&gt; 
    group_by({{group_var}}) |&gt; 
    summarize(mean({{mean_var}}))
}


